@node "Installation" "How to Install"

   @{fg fill}Automatically:@{fg text}
   Doubleclick the icon "Installation".
   The Installer ((c) Commodore, Inc.) will be started and installs
   all the macros, libraries and C:Programs.
   In addition a preferences-file will be created that contains the path
   to the online help files. (S:FW_Package.prefs).

   After that you can assign keyboard shortcuts or buttons to the macros
   as described in the FW-manual. 
   That's the best way to get quick access to the macros...

   @{fg fill}Manually:@{fg text}
   Please copy the following libraries in you LIBS: drawer: 
      reqtools.library     - (c) Nico FranÓois & Magnus Holmgren
      rexxreqtools.library - (c) Rafael D'Halleweyn
      triton.library       - (c) Stefan Zeiger
      tritonrexx.library   - (c) J■rgen Kohrmeyer

   @{fg shine}! Important !@{fg text} Please copy ALL the libraries. These
   are the latest versions from Aminet. So you can be sure that all macros will
   work perfectly.
 
   Please copy the following program to C:
      FlushTRX - ˋ J■rgen Kohrmeyer (belongs to the tritonrexx.library)

   The best thing is to copy the macros in your FWMacros drawer.
   After that you can assign keyboard shortcuts to them as described in
   your FW-manual.

   Create a file called "S:FW_Package.prefs" and there enter the path of the
   online-help files.

@endnode

